<br>
Further, the more aggro your MT generates, the more the entire rest of your raid can generate without attracting attention - so while it may not be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>needed</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> it is very very desirable to have a tank with dual EB so that your entire raid can maximize their DPS, making the mob dead faster.<br>
<br>
So in conclusion, Dual EB is &quot;nice to have&quot; - but not &quot;need to have&quot;, circumstances do change though and the higher you advance, the more damaging weapons will be acquired by your damage dealers and you will need more aggro to keep up with this, so the dual EB could change from &quot;nice&quot; to &quot;need&quot; at some point. <p><big><center><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19405 target=blank>Marshall Sscaley Iceblade</a><br><i><a href=http://companions.windsofstorm.net>The Companions ~ Team Headstart</a></i> <br>
